# challenge: socket

üìÖ 2025-09-19
üìÅ building a web server

---

## ‚úÖ what i did  
-clicked start
-opened the terminal
-ran: 'tmux'
-pressed: 'Ctrl+b + c'
-pressed: 'Ctrl+b + n'
-ran: 'grep -R socket /usr/include'
(in tmux to scroll the bar press Ctrl+b+[, to exit the scroll mode press q)
found out the syscall number for socket is 41
-ran: 'grep -R AF_INET /usr/include'
found out the AF_INET is defined into PF_INET macro
-ran: 'grep -R PF_INET /usr/include'
found out the PF_INET value is 2
-ran: 'grep -R SOCK_STREAM /usr/include'
found out the SOCK_STREAM value is 1
-pressed: 'Ctrl+b+p'
-ran: 'vim bro.s'
-typed: '.intel_syntax noprefix'
        '.global _start'
        '_start:'
        'mov rax, 41'
        'mov rdi, 2'
        'mov rsi, 1'
        'mov rdx, 0'
        'syscall'
        'mov rax, 60'
        'mov rdi, 0'
        'syscall'
-ran: 'as -o bro.o bro.s'
-ran: 'ld -o bro bro.o'
-ran: '/challenge/run bro'
-flag popped out

## üßëüèæ‚Äçüè´ what this challenge teaches u
the socket allows u to create a communication between client and server
the syscall number is 41 and takes 3 arguments:
rdi -> domain such as AF_INET, AF_INET6, AF_UNIX...
rsi -> type such as SOCK_STREAM (tcp) or SOCK_DGRAM (udp)
rdx -> protocol most of the time set to 0 as default
in this challenge grep -R helps u a lot to find out the actual value of AF_INET and SOCK_STREAM inside C's libreries
never forget to exit the program

